  <prompt>
    🚨 **CONDITIONAL TASK** — runs ONLY if Phase 1 task 012 (`012-resolve-insights-hold.poml`) returned outcome **(b) "we take the bug"** (per FR-05 sub-options in spec.md). For outcomes (a) sibling-takes-bug or (c) archived-pending-sibling-engagement, this task closes immediately with status `skipped-not-applicable` and a Notes entry pointing to `decisions/D-07-insights-layer2-resolution.md`.

    **Step 0 gate**: read `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/D-07-insights-layer2-resolution.md`. Confirm chosen outcome:
    - **(a) sibling-takes-bug** → task closes; RB-T028-02 already `transferred-to-sibling` in r1 ledger via task 012. STOP.
    - **(c) archived-pending-sibling-engagement** → task closes; RB-T028-02 already archived via task 012. STOP.
    - **(b) we-take-the-bug** → proceed to Step 1.

    If outcome (b): close real-bug-ledger entry **RB-T028-02** by fixing the Insights Layer 2 outcome-extraction LLM-mock fixture drift. 3 tests in the `Layer2OutcomeExtractionTests` class are Skip'd. The production file is `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/Extraction/Layer2OutcomeExtractor.cs` (verify exact path) — owned by `ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1` sibling project. Per the ledger §667: failures assert document-text round-trip through mock LLM — fixture-text drift, not production correctness issue.

    Per NFR-04 cite `RB-T028-02` + resolution mode `repaired`. Sibling-coordination: notify `ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1` owner BEFORE editing (D-07 should already have recorded the agreement to take the bug).
  </prompt>

