  <context>
    <background>
      Per the ledger §651-727: RB-T028-02 was placed on HOLD by Wave 0 task 008 of the predecessor (r1) pending sibling project sign-off (`ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1`). r2 Phase 1 task 012 resolves the HOLD via one of three outcomes (FR-05):
      - **(a)** sibling project takes the bug — 3 tests transferred; T028-02 closed with cross-reference
      - **(b)** r2 takes the bug — production fix here (this fallback task runs)
      - **(c)** archived-pending-sibling-engagement (1-week timeout — sibling unresponsive)

      Per ledger §667: failures assert document-text round-trip through mock LLM — this is fixture-text drift, NOT a production correctness issue. The documented zero-misroute invariant for Layer 2 is observed end-to-end via sibling integration tests. So if r2 takes the bug, the fix is likely surgical (fixture alignment or extractor projection adjustment) rather than a structural change.

      Per `notes/lessons-learned.md` r1 sibling-coordination pattern: notify the sibling owner BEFORE editing — D-07 should have recorded the agreement. If sibling has not signed off on outcome (b), this task BLOCKS until they do.
    </background>
