    <step order="4">Read the test file `Layer2OutcomeExtractionTests.cs` + the 3 Skip'd tests. Examine the TRX failure messages (excerpted in ledger §667). Identify whether the drift is in: (a) fixture text, (b) prompt template, (c) projection logic, or (d) `IObservationEmitter` chain.</step>
    <step order="5">Apply the surgical fix targeting the identified drift point. Coordinate with sibling owner if the fix touches sibling-internal contracts.</step>
    <step order="6">Remove `Skip = "..."` + per-test traits on the 3 affected tests.</step>
    <step order="7">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="8">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Layer2OutcomeExtraction"`. Confirm 3 tests pass.</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check`. Document sibling-coordination evidence in the PR description.</step>
    <step order="10">Update RB-T028-02 ledger: Status → `repaired` (if outcome b executed); cross-reference D-07 + sibling owner sign-off. Commit: `fix(ai/insights): align Layer 2 outcome-extraction fixture drift (RB-T028-02; repaired)`. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

